  "prompt": "What are philosophical quotes?",
  "response": "Philosophical quotes are thought-provoking statements that explore profound ideas about life, existence, knowledge, values, reason, and human nature. Here are some famous examples from different philosophers:\n\n1. Wisdom and Knowledge\n\u2022 \"I know that I know nothing\" - Socrates\n\u2022 \"The unexamined life is not worth living\" - Socrates\n\u2022 \"Cogito, ergo sum\" (I think, therefore I am) - Ren\u00e9 Descartes\n\n2. Life and Existence\n\u2022 \"Life is what happens to you while you're busy making other plans\" - Jean-Paul Sartre\n\u2022 \"Existence precedes essence\" - Jean-Paul Sartre\n\u2022 \"Man is condemned to be free\" - Jean-Paul Sartre\n\n3. Human Nature\n\u2022 \"Man is by nature a political animal\" - Aristotle\n\u2022 \"Hell is other people\" - Jean-Paul Sartre\n\u2022 \"To be is to be perceived\" - George Berkeley\n\n4. Personal Growth\n\u2022 \"Know thyself\" - Socrates\n\u2022 \"Be the change you wish to see in the world\" - Mahatma Gandhi\n\u2022 \"What doesn't kill you makes you stronger\" - Friedrich Nietzsche\n\n5. Ethics and Morality\n\u2022 \"Act only according to that maxim by which you can at the same time will that it should become a universal law\" - Immanuel Kant\n\nThese quotes typically encourage critical thinking and reflection on deeper meanings of life and human experience.",
